<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1641" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1641">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 816.001Ar1.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">President of Salvador</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The White House</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1913</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I am shocked to learn of the dastardly attempt on Your Excellency’s life
                            and hasten to express the hope of this Government and my personal
                            earnest wish for your speedy recovery.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">William Howard Taft</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>